<dl id="n08125h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08125h">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08125h"> 125(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> consolamentum</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">it is not the Catholic sacraments but the peculiar ceremony of the Albigenses known as the <i>consolamentum</i>, or &ldquo;consolation&rdquo;, that purifies the soul from all sin <small> <a name="CECRA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CECRA"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Coemgen&rdquo;, &ldquo;Rosary&rdquo; and &ldquo;Albigenses&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) I, &lsquo;Albigenses&rsquo; 268a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
